<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-082-052 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 155 345</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 15 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for PC: low-cost Japanese language translator. (SanyoElectric's Heaven JE/EJ)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miyazawa, Masayuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sanyo Electric Inc. (Product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentJapanese LanguageLanguage TranslationSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR PC: Low-Cost Japanese Language Translator 08/15/91 TOKYO, JAPAN, 1991AUG 15 (NB) -- Sanyo Electric has developed a PC-based language translationsystem which it claims provides high quality translation at a low cost.andM;The system was developed and runs on Sanyo's 32-bit PC.andP;  It can translatefrom English to Japanese and vice versa.andP;  Top speed for the software is 5,000words an hour from English to Japanese, and 4,000 words an hour in theopposite direction.andM;The system has a Japanese-English dictionary of 57,000 words, and anEnglish-Japanese dictionary of 50,000 words.andM;Called the &quot;Heaven JE/EJ,&quot; the system runs on most Intel 80386-based PCs, butrequires a minimum configuration of eight megabytes of RAM and a 40MB harddrive, running OS/2, to operate effectively.andM;The price of the whole system including the PC is expected to cost less than1 million yen ($7,400), a price that is extremely cheap for this type oflanguage translation system.andP;  Currently, most of the practical translationsystems run on workstations and cost 5 to 6 million yen ($40,000).andM;One of the major problems for language translation systems is the actualquality of the resultant translation.andP;  There has been a lot of wrangling inthe computer industry in the past few years, which was not helped whenBravice International of Tokyo, one of the industry's main suppliers oflanguage translation software, went bankrupt last year.andM;The Heaven JE/EJ is set to be released at the end of 1991.andM;(Masayuki Miyazawa/19910815/Press Contact: Sanyo, andplus;81-3-3835- 1111)</TEXT></DOC>